			<div data-wfedit="html" class="">
				<h3 style="text-align: left;">In our first formal residency partnership,&#160;BAM and Lumberyard
Contemporary Performing Arts will collaborate in&#160;commissioning and
nuturing three new dance pieces. Joe Melillo chose&#160;David Neumann, Kimberly
Bartosik, and Kaneza Schall to receive residencies at Lumberyard (formerly
known as the American Dance Institute) in Catskill, NY. Each will receive
$10,000 development fee, technical and dramaturgical support, housing, meals, and transportation.
&#160;The artists' work will premiere at Lumberyard in advance of the 2018 Next
Wave Festival. You can read more about this exciting partnership in today's <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/27/arts/dance/brooklyn-academy-of-music-lumberyard-dance-residencies.html?_r=0">New
York Times</a>.&#160;</h3></div>
		</div>
		<div data-wfcb="divider" data-wflabel="Divider" class="divider-block" draggable="false">
			<hr />
		</div>
		<div data-wfcb="text" data-wflabel="Text" class="text-block" draggable="false">
			<div data-wfedit="html" class="">
				<p align="left" style="text-align: left;" class="alt"><br /></p>
				<p class="" align="left" style="text-align: left;">R&B Festival at MetroTech 2017 (Jun 8-Aug 10) provides free outdoor music every Thursday at noon. Next week Grammy Award Winner and Brooklyn native, Cory Henry (Aug 3), performs with his six-member crew The Funk Apostles. The following week features
					Liv Warfield, Judith Hill, and Shelby J: Love 4 One Another (Aug 10). These three Prince prot&#233;g&#233;s have toured with Michael Jackson, D&#8217;Angelo, Santana, and Stevie Wonder. Come listen as they close out the festival with a big bang.</p>
			</div>
